'''I——内倾'''相对于外倾。INFP倾向于宁静和有所保留。于社交中，他们消耗能量（同样的情况下，外倾者获得能量）。<ref>{{cite web|url=http://changingminds.org/explanations/preferences/extravert_introvert.htm|title=Changing Minds: Extraversion vs. Introversion|accessdate=2011-02-02|archive-date=2011-03-08|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110308083548/http://changingminds.org/explanations/preferences/extravert_introvert.htm|dead-url=no}}</ref>

'''N——直觉'''相对于感觉。相比关心具体事物，INFP更加关心于抽象事物。他们更倾向于关注整体而不是细节，关注未来的可能性而非最切近的现实。<ref>{{cite web|url=http://changingminds.org/explanations/preferences/sensing_intuiting.htm|title=Changing Minds: Sensing vs. Intuiting|accessdate=2011-02-02|archive-date=2011-01-23|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110123220334/http://changingminds.org/explanations/preferences/sensing_intuiting.htm|dead-url=no}}</ref>

'''F——感情'''相对于理性。INFP通常认为个人偏好高于客观标准。在做决定的时候，他们通常更侧重于人情世故而非逻辑。<ref>{{cite web|url=http://changingminds.org/explanations/preferences/thinking_feeling.htm|title=Changing Minds: Thinking vs. Feeling|accessdate=2011-02-02|archive-date=2011-03-06|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110306115756/http://changingminds.org/explanations/preferences/thinking_feeling.htm|dead-url=no}}</ref>

'''P——理解'''相对于判斷。INFP会保留意见或推迟作出重要的决定，更倾向于“开放选择权”，更能应对变化。<ref>{{cite web|url=http://changingminds.org/explanations/preferences/judging_perceiving.htm|title=Changing Minds: Judging vs. Perceiving|accessdate=2011-02-02|archive-date=2011-03-02|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110302000451/http://changingminds.org/explanations/preferences/judging_perceiving.htm|dead-url=no}}</ref>

